Lands<br>
22 islands   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">from the name you can see the deck is based on one card, statsis.  now most ppl have never really faced statsis cause a) it looks weak to start or b)cant play it well.  statsis isnt a counterspell deck that just stops you by locking up what you play.  true statsis decks use counters to buy time between the time they draw it and are able to play it and keep it out.  after this they serve as a way to keep statsis out and protected.  most of the counterspells in this deck also have alternative castings costs so that you are able to keep islands untaped to a) pay the upkeep cost of statsis or b) fuel a capsize lock.  this deck works pretty well between all the draw and counterspells.  <br>
<br>
the reason i chose advanced for this deck wasnt the amount of rares but how to play the deck.  in my hands this deck goes 7 wins to every 10 games but if i lend it to a friend it drops to 3 to every 10 games.  even with my friends who have played agaisnt the deck numerous times have trouble knowoing what to counter, when to play the statsis.  should i gush early or later.  it jsut takes alot of time to learn the deck.<br>
<br>
sorry for the typos but thanks for reading <br>
gerry the nova </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
